  Locus:
    Page: 181
    Verse: 16
Tags:
  - Giving
---
The hoarder, who is anxiously worried about losing something, is,
psychologically speaking, the poor impoverished man, regardless of how
much he has. Whoever is capable of giving of himself is rich.
